title: Kel Tec PF9 9mm Handgun
postcontent:
I am selling my Kel Tec PF9 9mm handgun. It is in immaculate condition- there's not one scratch, it's spotless, and it works perfectly. I bought it brand new not even 6 months ago, and I have only put 28 rounds through it, so it's basically brand new. I have cleaned and oiled it several times because I just enjoy cleaning and assembling firearms (a hobby of mine). I'm selling because I don't use it as much as I thought I would, and it just sits in its case.

This is the flattest and most concealable 9mm handgun on the market today with a width of .88 inches. Kel Tec made it specifically for its concealment, but when fired, it shoots just like a full-sized handgun. It comes with the Kel Tec PF9 handgun itself, a 7 round magazine, a trigger lock, and a belt clip that is attached to the handgun which allows you to conceal carry in your pants without the use of a holster (you can see it in the first picture on the side of the gun.  It is removable if you don't want it on there...and it IS a Kel Tec part, not some homemade attachment. It's a $22 part, but it was well worth it.). This is the newer model PF9 so it comes with an accessory rail in front of the trigger. All this comes in the original case with the instruction booklet.  Kel Tec has a lifetime warranty on their firearms, as well. MSRP for the Kel Tec PF9 is $319-$333, but I'm selling for $260. If you have any questions, feel free to email me. Thanks for your interest.

This handsome rimfire rifle sports an AR-style look and is modeled after the legendary original Colt M4. A "Tactical Rimfire" rifle, the M4 Ops is an upgraded version of the .22 M4 Carbine. postcontent: I am no expert, but I had a gunsmith look at this to see about putting a scope on it, and he said it was a Sweedish Mauser that had been heavily modified. I just want a scope on one, and I was told by the gunsmith that it would actually DEvalue this gun to drill and tap for scope mounts. It has the older sights with adjustment for windage and elevation. It is a really nice piece and would go great for someone who collects this type of thing. Ideally, I would like to trade this for or possibly towards another 30-06 that has a scope or at least provisions to easily put a scope on it. If I didn't trade straight up, I wouldn't be able to put a whole lot of boot with it, meaning I am NOT looking for a $1000 gold plated mantle piece or something. I am looking for something that doesn't mind or has even seen some use. I would sell it for the price listed, but just to use the money to buy another 30-06. title: Barrett M82A1 CQ Semi-Automatic (20 Inch Barrel)
postcontent:
Brand New!  Never been fired.  Comes with Leupold Scope Rings and Two Boxes of Ammo.  This is absolutely Beautiful!!!

The Model 82A1 series rifle is a rugged, dependable semi-automatic rifle. In simple terms, it has earned unmatched respect because it works in battlefield conditions. Our military men and women have depended on over 5,000 Model 82A1rifles to protect themselves and to protect our freedoms. 

Unlike other semi-automatic .50 BMG's, the Model 82A1 is completely reliable. Its chamber is chrome plated and dimensioned for both civilian and military ammunition. The extractor and ejector are proven to work under any condition. Close tolerances on all parts and intelligent design allows it to function in all environments. The trigger is appropriate for a battle rifle. 

The improved muzzle brake, along with dual barrel springs and a long mainspring design make the Model 82A1 comfortable and fun to shoot. Rapid, accurate fire from its ten round magazine is a breeze. 

The Model 82A1 fits in a regular sized carry case. It is transported disassembled as an upper and lower receiver. The rifle is assembled and ready to fire in under a minute by inserting 2 assembly pins through both receivers. Since the scope remains mounted on the upper receiver, the scope zero is maintained. The Model 82A1's M1913 optics rail is elevated 27 MOA to take full advantage of a scope's elevation travel. Emergency iron sights are provided as well. 

For over 2 decades, the short-recoil, semi-automatic Model 82A1 series has been refined and improved. There are no competitors. 

The Model 82A1 is what you expect in a Barrett. Dependable. Reliable. Well-designed.

**** ammo has been sold, price is now $850 for everything****

Up for sale is my recently built AR. (sorry for the wall of text, just thought I'd put enough information so you know what I'm lookin for)

There is a tiny bit of wear on the hammer from hand cycling, but it has never actually fired a round. There is space in the back of the stock for 4 CR123 batteries for a mountable flashlight, and space for 2 more of said batteries in the pistol grip.

 It will come with five 30 round magazines (3 of them are normal steel magazines, the other 2 are windowed P-Mags).

The upper is $600, or trade for any of the guns above or cash, or a combination of the two, whatever is easiest for you. 

Other things I would be interested in trading for that aren't firearm related are RC cars (nitro or electric) + cash, or a ps3 bundle with Metal Gear Solid 4 + cash.

Face to face only, I will not ship any part of this weapon. Also, please don't contact me wanting to make a deal, then back out and decide that you aren't going to tell me, that just wastes my time as well as yours.

postcontent:

Excellent condition over all with a few handling marks.  The action locks up well.  I will mention that the cylinder gap is very tight. title: AR-15_A1 5.56 mm Pre-Ban
postcontent:
For Trade: AR-15_A1 5.56 mm Pre-Ban
Want a larger caliber (.308+) AR-10 in trade or a good cash offer so I can purchase one. I prefer Armalite, but there are many great gun manufacturers here in the USA.

Upper: Colt 20-inch barrel 1:9 twist w/ bayonet lug. Barrel marked "C MP Chrome Bore"; C for the manufacturer Colt, MP stamp means the barrel was magnafluxed and proofed, chrome bore and chamber. (Bolt stamped with SE inside an 8 sided octagon).

Lower: PWA (Pac West Arms, Milan, Ill.; this was the early LMT company I believe and Rock River Arms bought out PWA. From everything that I have heard they are excellent lowers!) 5.56mm Commando. This is a forged lower not cast. Serial# 11174. (PWA post-ban have a year prefix in the serial number. The serial # cutoff was 35222 for preban status).

Standard two point sling. Has a new AR-16 cleaning kit in the butt stock storage compartment. Have one USA 30 round AR-15 .223 magazine by O'Kay Industries, Inc., New Britain, Conn.

This AR is in great shape and supreme working order. I had it fully serviced (new parts, fired & cleaned) by a gunsmith at Anderson's Gun Repair Shop here in Springfield, MO before putting it up for sale; new extractor spring & gas tube (had a dent in the tube which slowed the gas pressure).

I've had this same rifle (but fully auto - M16) issued to me during the latter part of the Vietnam conflict. I hate to part with this, but with the times as they are now I would prefer a much larger caliber for home defense. Not worried about whether or not you can hunt with it.

Let me know what you have and I'll see if we can come to an agreement.
